
[1]cessation

   CESSATION, n.

   1. A ceasing; a stop; a rest; the act of discontinuing motion or action
   of any kind, whether temporary or final.

   2. A ceasing or suspension of operation, force or effect; as a
   cessation of the laws of nature.

   A cessation of arms, an armistice or truce, agreed to by the commanders
   of armies, to give time for a capitulation, or for other purposes.
